      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: shard local Swift tests",
        "body": "## Summary\n- route local full-suite test entry points through the existing suite-shard runner\n- preserve CI's one-suite isolation through wrapper environment overrides\n- align active contributor and release docs on `make test`\n\nThe aggregate `swift test` process is not hermetic under this repository's shared AppKit/global-state test load: independent suites pass, while a monolithic run can produce timing-dependent cross-suite failures. Sharding contains that state while retaining the same discovered test coverage.\n\n## Validation\n- `python3 Scripts/ci_swift_test_by_suite.py --group-size 12 --timeout 180` (441 suites passed)\n- `./Scripts/test.sh --limit-groups 1`\n- wrapper invoked from `/tmp` with `--list-only` (441 suites discovered)\n- `make check`\n- `bash -n Scripts/test.sh Scripts/compile_and_run.sh Scripts/prepare_upstream_pr.sh`\n- `git diff --check`\n- local autoreview: clean\n\n\n## Follow-up hardening\n- local batched runs retry one identical non-timeout shard once; a repeated failure remains fatal\n- timeout fallback still isolates suites one at a time\n- fake-Swift regression covers transient recovery and repeated-failure propagation\n- exact local `make test` passed all 441 suites; shard 12 reproduced the known timing failure once, the identical retry passed, and the run completed\n",
        "branch": "fix/local-test-sharding",
